text: Hi! How are you doing today?
Hi there, I am doing ok how are you?
I'm not doing too bad. Thank you!
How has you day gone today?
Not too bad, I just got in from work a few minutes ago. I'm glad it's almost the weekend.
Yes, I always look forward to the weekend.  Now college football is fixing to start up and I am even happier!
Yes it is. College football and a 3 day weekend. It can't get much better than that. Who's your team?
I am born and bred TCU football so they are and will always be my team, what about you?
I'm an Auburn fan myself.
How do you think they are going to do this year?  I know Alabama is going to be tough as usual

I think they'll do ok. I expect them to stay at least in the top 15. They're a young team this year, but it seems like they always are. Our QB has had some shoulder issues this offseason so we'll see how that plays out. Our run game should be strong though. Alabama is going to be tough as long as Saban has a hand in that organization.
Isnt Stidham your QB still or is he graduated, I know he was from Baylor and really good!
Yeah he's still there. He did really well last year.
Nice, well we play Ohio State and I think 99% of the country is going to be rooting for us to win because of Urban Meyer lol.
Yeah, hopefully you guys will. Urban's going to be the nasty face of CFB this year.
I just cant believe the flimsy excuses by the university to be honest, all they really care about is winning.
Yeah that's the way it is these days. It's sad.
besides auburn obviously, who would you pick in the final 4 playoffs?
I think it'll be Alabama of course, I'd like to see TCU, you guys always seem to be a contender, I'd like to see Michigan, and anyone but Clemson lol.
Haha, my sleeper team is West Virginia I think they have a chance to be really good, their QB might be the best pro prospect this season.  I think we will finish in the top3 of the B-12.
I'd like to see someone else besides an SEC team win it honestly. This coming from an unbiased SEC fan.
That is nice, I agree with you about Clemson though, it should be fun though regardless!
Yeah it should be. It's been nice talking to you. I guess I should get to the point of the chat. Would you like to donate any of your earnings to Save The Children?
Sure they are a reputable charity and I have seen their work on TV.  I would be willing to donate 0.75 of mine no question.
Thank you for you donation. Good luck to your team this year! Go Frogs!
Good luck to you too, Go Tigers!
